{
  "doc_id": "50345",
  "text": "Many studies have investigated the relationship between microsatellites and stable genetic markers (such as Alu insertions and SNPs) in an attempt to deduce common patterns of LD in different human populations. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] These data suggest that, at least in non-African populations, highly significant LD persists for a considerable genetic distance between microsatellites and stable markers, suggesting that microsatellites may be useful for identifying disease loci by association analysis.",
